{"query": {"id": "1611376951191-46f9071f817f696a", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=b99a62882589871e&fccid=64a03460056ca566&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Local Landcare Coordinator - Lake Cargelligo", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Lake Cargelligo, NSW"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-12T04:42:39.773007", "description": "Title:\n\nLocal Landcare Coordinator - Lake Cargelligo\n\nAdvertiser:\n\nLake Cowal Foundation\n\nLocation:\n\nLake Cargelligo, NSW\n\nSalary etc:\n\nPart time temporary position 19.6 hours/week (0.5 FTE) to June 2023\n\nThe Position: Lake Cargelligo Landcare and the Lake Cowal Foundation (Local Landcare Coordinator host organisation) is seeking a motivated and enthusiastic person who is interested in people, sustainable production and the environment, to work in Lake Cargelligo and the surrounding area. Local Landcare Coordinators work to support existing Landcare groups and facilitate general local community awareness and engagement with natural resource management. The coordinator is part of a virtual team of local coordinators who work within the LachIan catchment.\n\nPosition/role objectives: The Local Coordinator is that of an enabler for local community volunteer Landcare. Local Coordinators will work with their host organisation, local steering committee, and the Landcare groups and organisations of their area to support and empower them to achieve their own goals, to participate in Landcare, to partner with Local Land Services and to deliver on the target outcomes of the NSW Landcare Program.\n\nLinks to existing programs: The Local Landcare Coordinator Initiative meshes with existing team members and the support arrangements currently in place through the Regional Landcare Facilitator Network. Regional Landcare Facilitators play an important role in facilitating a community of practice and in assisting with the collection and aggregation of data from each region. The Landcare Support Program Manager and the State Landcare Coordinator work with each Local Land Services region and the Landcare community in the region to identify current programs and existing support roles and to ensure linkages occur.\n\nCompetencies:\n\nis proactive with a community-minded attitude\nhas excellent networking and people skills\nhas good project management, communication, coordination, administration and computing skills\nhas a strong interest in and commitment to local agricultural land management and environmental issues\ncan manage their workload effectively\nis flexible about their working hours over the period of employment\nhas a current driver’s licence.\n\nSelection criteria:\n\nSound understanding of natural resource management issues in the region and understanding of the local community.\nDemonstrated well-developed written and oral communication skills, including competence in the use of Word, Excel, email and the Internet.\nDemonstrated ability to work with and develop community groups, including group facilitation, action planning and mediation skills.\nProven expertise in project planning, management, record keeping and report writing.\nDemonstrated ability to work with minimum supervision, use initiative and work as part of a team or network.\nProven ability to build partnerships with government agencies, non -government agencies, community groups and landholders, including schools and indigenous groups.\nExperience in Natural Resource Management, Environmental Science, Sustainable Agriculture or similar.\nAbility and willingness to work outside office hours to contact landholders and attend community group meetings.", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<p>Title:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Local Landcare Coordinator - Lake Cargelligo</strong></p>\n\n<p>Advertiser:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Lake Cowal Foundation</strong></p>\n\n<p>Location:</p>\n\n<p>Lake Cargelligo, NSW</p>\n\n<p>Salary etc:</p>\n\n<p>Part time temporary position 19.6 hours/week (0.5 FTE) to June 2023</p>\n\n<p><strong>The Position: </strong>Lake Cargelligo Landcare and the Lake Cowal Foundation (Local Landcare Coordinator host organisation) is seeking a motivated and enthusiastic person who is interested in people, sustainable production and the environment, to work in Lake Cargelligo and the surrounding area. Local Landcare Coordinators work to support existing Landcare groups and facilitate general local community awareness and engagement with natural resource management. The coordinator is part of a virtual team of local coordinators who work within the LachIan catchment.</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nPosition/role objectives: </strong>The Local Coordinator is that of an enabler for local community volunteer Landcare. Local Coordinators will work with their host organisation, local steering committee, and the Landcare groups and organisations of their area to support and empower them to achieve their own goals, to participate in Landcare, to partner with Local Land Services and to deliver on the target outcomes of the NSW Landcare Program.</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nLinks to existing programs: </strong>The Local Landcare Coordinator Initiative meshes with existing team members and the support arrangements currently in place through the Regional Landcare Facilitator Network. Regional Landcare Facilitators play an important role in facilitating a community of practice and in assisting with the collection and aggregation of data from each region. The Landcare Support Program Manager and the State Landcare Coordinator work with each Local Land Services region and the Landcare community in the region to identify current programs and existing support roles and to ensure linkages occur.</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nCompetencies:</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>is proactive with a community-minded attitude</li>\n<li>has excellent networking and people skills</li>\n<li>has good project management, communication, coordination, administration and computing skills</li>\n<li>has a strong interest in and commitment to local agricultural land management and environmental issues</li>\n<li>can manage their workload effectively</li>\n<li>is flexible about their working hours over the period of employment</li>\n<li>has a current driver’s licence.</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Selection criteria:</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Sound understanding of natural resource management issues in the region and understanding of the local community.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated well-developed written and oral communication skills, including competence in the use of Word, Excel, email and the Internet.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to work with and develop community groups, including group facilitation, action planning and mediation skills.</li>\n<li>Proven expertise in project planning, management, record keeping and report writing.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to work with minimum supervision, use initiative and work as part of a team or network.</li>\n<li>Proven ability to build partnerships with government agencies, non -government agencies, community groups and landholders, including schools and indigenous groups.</li>\n<li>Experience in Natural Resource Management, Environmental Science, Sustainable Agriculture or similar.</li>\n<li>Ability and willingness to work outside office hours to contact landholders and attend community group meetings.</li></ul>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9861324, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b99a62882589871e&from=serp&vjs=3", "employmentType": "Part-time", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "Lake Cowal Foundation"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951191-2d3a246f1a6a7a6e", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=cc40457148c674b9&fccid=5a1a9fb9972c67fd&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Category Insights Manager", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Hawthorn East VIC 3123"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-06T04:42:40.303833", "description": "Requisition ID: 8818\n\nEmployment Type: Full time\n\nGood things start here\n\nThis could be the very first step towards an exciting new career with us – a fresh beginning. At the Coles Group, these are moments we live for.\n\nStarting good things is what drives our purpose: to sustainably feed all Australians so they can lead healthier, happier lives. With a team of 120,000 people and an iconic portfolio of Australia’s most trusted brands, we’re perfectly positioned to turn a promising start into a whole lot more.\n\nAs one of biggest brands in Australia, we connect with over 19 million people each week. Whether it’s innovative in-store design, creative omnichannel storytelling, or thunderclap advertising that reaches 98% of Australians, our Marketing team play a pivotal role in driving our brand forward, helping our customers lead healthier and happier lives, and building the trust and reliability we’re known for.\n\nAbout the role\n\nSitting within our Customer Behaviour team, you will drive customer obsession within the category teams by delivering a thorough understanding of the customer and translating customer behaviour and needs into key commercial and actionable insights. You will build team member capability and enable all team members to make customer obsessed decisions every day at Coles.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\nReporting to the Senior Category Insight manager, you will support major strategic category projects, such as category planning and category acceleration, to drive customer-led strategies. You will also build stakeholders capability around customer insights in order to support them as they self-serve and develop a richer understanding of the customer.\n\nYou’ll also:\n\nProvide thought leadership regarding the consumer, our customers, product categories, competitors, and the economic environment.\nWork closely with Research and Analytics team to implement appropriate research and analytics methods and tools to understand customer perceptions and behaviour as well as Customer Care to action feedback.\nManage external agencies and consultancies in the delivery of the agreed insights, strategy and research agenda.\nIdentify and deliver improvements to optimise deliverables and processes\n\nGood things you’ll need\n\nWe’re after a customer obsessed and data driven customer research, insights and analytics professional with a strong interest in project related work as well as coaching and training team members in all thing’s customer.\n\nYou’ll also need:\n\nSolid expertise in synthesizing complex data sets to uncover actionable Customer Insights\nExperience building capability and embedding self-serve tools\nExperience leveraging and enabling others to use 3rd party customer data (i.e. Nielsen, IRI, Quantium), data visualisation platforms (i.e. Power BI, Tableau) and Voice of Customer platforms (i.e. Qualtrics, Medallia)\nExperience designing and executing Customer Research projects (both quantitative and qualitative data) including experimental design and a working knowledge of statistical analyses\nKnowledge of behavioural science and consumer psychology is highly desirable\nExperience in working in retail/FMCG is highly desirable\n\nWhy Coles?\nWe’re committed to making this a great place to work, from day one. From flexible working arrangements to discounts across all our internal brands (including 5% off at Coles supermarkets!), there are plenty of reasons to love working here. Explore all this and more at our Coles Careers website.\n\nFor everyone who shares our passion\nWe encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, abilities and cultures – including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, the LGBTQI+ community and people living with disability. We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support accessibility needs – so reach out to us at www.careers.colesgroup.com.au > Careers for everyone > Disability employment.\n\nWe’d love to meet you\nIf you have the skills, experience and motivation to succeed in this role, please take the next step and submit your application.", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<p>Requisition ID: 8818</p>\n\n<p>Employment Type: Full time</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>Good things start here</strong></p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>This could be the very first step towards an exciting new career with us – a fresh beginning. At the Coles Group, these are moments we live for.<br></p>\n\n<p>Starting good things is what drives our purpose: to sustainably feed all Australians so they can lead healthier, happier lives. With a team of 120,000 people and an iconic portfolio of Australia’s most trusted brands, we’re perfectly positioned to turn a promising start into a whole lot more.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>As one of biggest brands in Australia, we connect with over 19 million people each week. Whether it’s innovative in-store design, creative omnichannel storytelling, or thunderclap advertising that reaches 98% of Australians, our Marketing team play a pivotal role in driving our brand forward, helping our customers lead healthier and happier lives, and building the trust and reliability we’re known for.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>About the role</strong></p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Sitting within our Customer Behaviour team, you will drive customer obsession within the category teams by delivering a thorough understanding of the customer and translating customer behaviour and needs into key commercial and actionable insights. You will build team member capability and enable all team members to make customer obsessed decisions every day at Coles.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>What you’ll be doing</strong></p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Reporting to the Senior Category Insight manager, you will support major strategic category projects, such as category planning and category acceleration, to drive customer-led strategies. You will also build stakeholders capability around customer insights in order to support them as they self-serve and develop a richer understanding of the customer.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>You’ll also:</p>\n\n<ul><li>Provide thought leadership regarding the consumer, our customers, product categories, competitors, and the economic environment.</li>\n<li>Work closely with Research and Analytics team to implement appropriate research and analytics methods and tools to understand customer perceptions and behaviour as well as Customer Care to action feedback.</li>\n<li>Manage external agencies and consultancies in the delivery of the agreed insights, strategy and research agenda.</li>\n<li>Identify and deliver improvements to optimise deliverables and processes</li></ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>Good things you’ll need</strong></p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>We’re after a customer obsessed and data driven customer research, insights and analytics professional with a strong interest in project related work as well as coaching and training team members in all thing’s customer.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>You’ll also need:</p>\n\n<ul><li>Solid expertise in synthesizing complex data sets to uncover actionable Customer Insights\n</li><li>Experience building capability and embedding self-serve tools</li>\n<li>Experience leveraging and enabling others to use 3rd party customer data (i.e. Nielsen, IRI, Quantium), data visualisation platforms (i.e. Power BI, Tableau) and Voice of Customer platforms (i.e. Qualtrics, Medallia)</li>\n<li>Experience designing and executing Customer Research projects (both quantitative and qualitative data) including experimental design and a working knowledge of statistical analyses</li>\n<li>Knowledge of behavioural science and consumer psychology is highly desirable</li>\n<li>Experience in working in retail/FMCG is highly desirable</li></ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>Why Coles?</strong><br>\nWe’re committed to making this a great place to work, from day one. From flexible working arrangements to discounts across all our internal brands (including 5% off at Coles supermarkets!), there are plenty of reasons to love working here. Explore all this and more at our Coles Careers website.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>For everyone who shares our passion</strong><br>\nWe encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, abilities and cultures – including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, the LGBTQI+ community and people living with disability. We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support accessibility needs – so reach out to us at www.careers.colesgroup.com.au &gt; Careers for everyone &gt; Disability employment.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>We’d love to meet you</strong><br>\nIf you have the skills, experience and motivation to succeed in this role, please take the next step and submit your application.</p>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.97717947, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cc40457148c674b9&from=serp&vjs=3", "employmentType": "Full time", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "Coles Careers"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951229-074633504fdf0cb2", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=e18f8f2eb9cc123b&fccid=c1265cfdd3841ac9&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Environment Manager", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Melbourne, Australia"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-22T04:42:40.192850", "description": "Position No: 2699GRE\nDivision: Global Real Estate\nLocation: Melbourne, Australia\nWork Type: Open Term - Full Time\nApplications Close: 07/02/2021 6:00 PM\n\nThe opportunity\n\nWe have a full time open term opportunity for an Environment Manager to join QIC’s Global Real Estate (GRE) team to be based in Melbourne, however would also consider applicants to be based from our Sydney or Brisbane office.\n\nReporting to the General Manager – Sustainability, your role is responsible for developing and implementing the environmental sustainability elements of GRE’s ESG strategy. This includes development and delivery of continuous improvement programs across GRE’s asset portfolio for key environmental performance categories including energy, water and waste, establishing and maintaining GRE’s ESG data and reporting system and processes and managing GRE’s annual and adhoc ESG and sustainability reporting and benchmarking obligations.\n\nThe role is key in developing and implementing large and complex programs aligned to GRE’s ESG Strategy to drive environmental sustainability across the business and achieve the company’s ESG commitments. You will additionally be responsible for assessing and quantifying the financial impacts of climate change across GRE’s asset portfolio and supporting Centre Teams to establish climate resilience adaptation plans to drive the implementation of relevant initiatives..\n\nYour role will also be responsible for the following key deliverables:\n\nMonitoring performance against and guiding the delivery of GRE’s Net Zero carbon emissions by 2028 target.\nEstablishing and managing ESG data and reporting processes and systems to ensure GRE maintains accurate, auditable and up to date ESG data (in consultation with the GRE BPT Data Team).\nEstablishing and managing third party assurance for GRE’s ESG data.\nManaging GRE’s environmental sustainability reporting and benchmarking obligations including (but not limited to) annual GRE ESG Report, GRESB Reports, NGERS, NABERS and Green Star.\nMonitoring and analysing GRE’s environmental sustainability performance, identifying asset and portfolio-wide programs to drive improvements and supporting Centre Teams to deliver agreed initiatives.\nKeeping abreast of environmental sustainability trends, industry developments and competitor performance.\nReporting on GRE’s environmental sustainability performance internally, and providing recommendations at an asset level and to GRE management on continuous improvement.\nRepresenting GRE in external forums to promote our own ESG credentials and ensure our approach remains in keeping with industry best practice.\nIn consultation with the General Manager – Sustainability, build effective partnerships with external stakeholders to support the achievement of GRE’s ESG Strategy.\nMonitor and record environmental incidents/breaches and ensure corrective/preventative action is carried out.\n\nThe ideal candidate\n\nAs a strong candidate for this role, you will have at least seven years knowledge, skills and experience in a similar role with solid experience in developing, managing and implementing environmental sustainability programs in large complex organisations with well-regarded sustainability agendas. You will also have Tertiary and/or post graduate qualifications in a relevant discipline (e.g. environmental science, sustainability, environmental management or related discipline).\n\nYou must also be able to demonstrate an in-depth understanding of the following:\n\nPassion for ESG activities and a previous track record of successfully working across complex businesses to deliver measurable environmental sustainability outcomes, including across the energy, water, waste, net zero carbon and climate resilience spaces.\nDemonstrated understanding of data and reporting and a previous track record of developing and implementing auditable ESG data management processes and systems.\nStrong computer and Microsoft Excel skills, including maintaining data with a high degree of accuracy and previous experience with third party assurance activities.\nExperience in promoting the benefits of ESG and negotiating with and influencing people at various levels of the organisation, from senior management, investment specialists, clients and external stakeholders.\nStrong project management skills including the ability to manage multiple deadlines and take ownership of initiatives and implement across the organisation.\nStrong stakeholder management skills including demonstrated ability to create trusted relationships with team members across the entire business.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills.\nCommercial, creative and pragmatic thinking about improving ESG practices and ability to exercise sound and practical judgement.\nDemonstrated technical knowledge of global sustainability reporting, global standards and measurement frameworks and property-based rating systems.\nPrevious real estate sector experience is highly regarded.\n\nQIC\n\nQIC is a leading long-term specialist manager in alternatives with a focus on infrastructure, real estate and private capital. We also specialise in liquid market solutions, providing multi-asset portfolios, liquid alternatives, active fixed interest and tailored overlays for our clients.\n\nWe’re high-performing and care about our clients, our colleagues and society at large. Headquartered in Brisbane, QIC is one of the largest institutional investment managers in Australia with over 800 employees across Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne, New York, Los Angeles, Cleveland, San Francisco, London and Copenhagen.\n\nLife at QIC\n\nQIC values and embraces differences and is committed to building an inclusive culture as we know our people do their best when they bring their whole self to work. Our commitment is represented through initiatives including our Reconciliation Action Plan and employee-led diversity networks promoting LGBTI, young professionals and gender equality.\n\nThe wellbeing of our employees is at our core. We support your personal development, family and interests while empowering flexibility through initiatives such as; fitness reimbursements, wellness studio, study assistance and generous parental leave. At QIC, we know flexibility means something different to everyone; talk to us about what flexibility means to you. Click here for more information on benefits to support your QIC career journey.\n\nTo apply\n\nTo apply, please submit a cover letter and CV via our career’s portal. QIC is a fast-moving organisation so we may start reviewing applications before the job advert closes.\n\nWe encourage you to visit QIC and follow QIC LinkedIn for more information and the latest industry news.\n\nAgencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by QIC’s Talent Acquisition team. Your respect for this process is appreciated.", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<p><strong>Position No:</strong> 2699GRE\n<br>\n<strong>Division:</strong> Global Real Estate\n<br>\n<strong>Location:</strong> Melbourne, Australia\n<br>\n<strong>Work Type:</strong> Open Term - Full Time\n<br>\n<strong>Applications Close:</strong> 07/02/2021 6:00 PM</p>\n\n<p><strong>The opportunity</strong></p>\n\n<p>We have a full time open term opportunity for an Environment Manager to join QIC’s Global Real Estate (GRE) team to be based in Melbourne, however would also consider applicants to be based from our Sydney or Brisbane office.</p>\n\n<p>Reporting to the General Manager – Sustainability, your role is responsible for developing and implementing the environmental sustainability elements of GRE’s ESG strategy. This includes development and delivery of continuous improvement programs across GRE’s asset portfolio for key environmental performance categories including energy, water and waste, establishing and maintaining GRE’s ESG data and reporting system and processes and managing GRE’s annual and adhoc ESG and sustainability reporting and benchmarking obligations.</p>\n\n<p>The role is key in developing and implementing large and complex programs aligned to GRE’s ESG Strategy to drive environmental sustainability across the business and achieve the company’s ESG commitments. You will additionally be responsible for assessing and quantifying the financial impacts of climate change across GRE’s asset portfolio and supporting Centre Teams to establish climate resilience adaptation plans to drive the implementation of relevant initiatives..</p>\n\n<p>Your role will also be responsible for the following key deliverables:</p>\n\n<ul><li>Monitoring performance against and guiding the delivery of GRE’s Net Zero carbon emissions by 2028 target.</li>\n<li>Establishing and managing ESG data and reporting processes and systems to ensure GRE maintains accurate, auditable and up to date ESG data (in consultation with the GRE BPT Data Team).</li>\n<li>Establishing and managing third party assurance for GRE’s ESG data.</li>\n<li>Managing GRE’s environmental sustainability reporting and benchmarking obligations including (but not limited to) annual GRE ESG Report, GRESB Reports, NGERS, NABERS and Green Star.</li>\n<li>Monitoring and analysing GRE’s environmental sustainability performance, identifying asset and portfolio-wide programs to drive improvements and supporting Centre Teams to deliver agreed initiatives.</li>\n<li>Keeping abreast of environmental sustainability trends, industry developments and competitor performance.</li>\n<li>Reporting on GRE’s environmental sustainability performance internally, and providing recommendations at an asset level and to GRE management on continuous improvement.</li>\n<li>Representing GRE in external forums to promote our own ESG credentials and ensure our approach remains in keeping with industry best practice.</li>\n<li>In consultation with the General Manager – Sustainability, build effective partnerships with external stakeholders to support the achievement of GRE’s ESG Strategy.</li>\n<li>Monitor and record environmental incidents/breaches and ensure corrective/preventative action is carried out.</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>The ideal candidate</strong></p>\n\n<p>As a strong candidate for this role, you will have at least seven years knowledge, skills and experience in a similar role with solid experience in developing, managing and implementing environmental sustainability programs in large complex organisations with well-regarded sustainability agendas. You will also have Tertiary and/or post graduate qualifications in a relevant discipline (e.g. environmental science, sustainability, environmental management or related discipline).</p>\n\n<p>You must also be able to demonstrate an in-depth understanding of the following:</p>\n\n<ul><li>Passion for ESG activities and a previous track record of successfully working across complex businesses to deliver measurable environmental sustainability outcomes, including across the energy, water, waste, net zero carbon and climate resilience spaces.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated understanding of data and reporting and a previous track record of developing and implementing auditable ESG data management processes and systems.</li>\n<li>Strong computer and Microsoft Excel skills, including maintaining data with a high degree of accuracy and previous experience with third party assurance activities.</li>\n<li>Experience in promoting the benefits of ESG and negotiating with and influencing people at various levels of the organisation, from senior management, investment specialists, clients and external stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Strong project management skills including the ability to manage multiple deadlines and take ownership of initiatives and implement across the organisation.</li>\n<li>Strong stakeholder management skills including demonstrated ability to create trusted relationships with team members across the entire business.</li>\n<li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li>\n<li>Commercial, creative and pragmatic thinking about improving ESG practices and ability to exercise sound and practical judgement.</li>\n<li>Demonstrated technical knowledge of global sustainability reporting, global standards and measurement frameworks and property-based rating systems.</li>\n<li>Previous real estate sector experience is highly regarded.</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>QIC</strong></p>\n\n<p>QIC is a leading long-term specialist manager in alternatives with a focus on infrastructure, real estate and private capital. We also specialise in liquid market solutions, providing multi-asset portfolios, liquid alternatives, active fixed interest and tailored overlays for our clients.</p>\n\n<p>We’re high-performing and care about our clients, our colleagues and society at large. Headquartered in Brisbane, QIC is one of the largest institutional investment managers in Australia with over 800 employees across Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne, New York, Los Angeles, Cleveland, San Francisco, London and Copenhagen.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Life at QIC</strong></p>\n\n<p>QIC values and embraces differences and is committed to building an inclusive culture as we know our people do their best when they bring their whole self to work. Our commitment is represented through initiatives including our Reconciliation Action Plan and employee-led diversity networks promoting LGBTI, young professionals and gender equality.</p>\n\n<p>The wellbeing of our employees is at our core. We support your personal development, family and interests while empowering flexibility through initiatives such as; fitness reimbursements, wellness studio, study assistance and generous parental leave. At QIC, we know flexibility means something different to everyone; talk to us about what flexibility means to you. Click here for more information on benefits to support your QIC career journey.</p>\n\n<p><strong>To apply</strong></p>\n\n<p>To apply, please submit a cover letter and CV via our career’s portal. QIC is a fast-moving organisation so we may start reviewing applications before the job advert closes.</p>\n\n<p>We encourage you to visit QIC and follow QIC LinkedIn for more information and the latest industry news.</p>\n\n<p><em>Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by QIC’s Talent Acquisition team. Your respect for this process is appreciated.</em></p>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9859474, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e18f8f2eb9cc123b&from=serp&vjs=3", "employmentType": "Open Term - Full Time", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "QIC Limited"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951228-8b9efa809832d0e9", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=b49e0aac8f882d5c&fccid=958c23dcfb7e66c7&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "NEC SG - Advisory/Software Engineer", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Australia"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-30T00:00:00", "description": "Advisory/Software Engineer (Fresh Graduates are welcome to apply)\n\nThe Open Innovation Center (OIC) of Global Safety Division (GSD) leads disruptive idea generation, research, testing and prototyping with the goal of launching breakthrough products and services inspired by global trends and emerging technologies, contributing to a Safer City.\n\nWork location is at 21 Biopolis Road #05-01/02 Nucleos (nearest MRT station: One North or Buona Vista).\n\nResponsibilities\n\nActively engage in the creation of new disruptive and transformational products and services.\nSenior members will lead squads (scrum teams) dedicated in the implementation of Proof-of-Concepts (POCs), Prototypes and Pilots with strategic customers.\nPromote customer advocacy by engaging with strategic customers, country affiliates and business partners on the formulation of POCs, Prototypes and Pilots in associated documentation.\nSupport the Technology Development Managers / Directors to prioritize concept requests at each stage of the OIC process (e.g. ideation, concept validation, agile prototyping).\nHands-on Involvement in the roadmap planning, design, architecting and coding of the POCs, Prototypes and Pilots.\nEngage in the whole DevOps lifecycle from the development, testing, deployment, maintenance and operations of products and services.\nParticipate in the building and enhancement of a robust pipeline to support the automation of various development associated tasks to achieve continuous integration and delivery.\nProactively devise innovative solutions by constantly broadening and deepening the skillsets, and attaining awareness of trends and development in the technical domain to address latent challenges faced by various industries.\nIdentify best practices from industry and implement new and evolve methodology as appropriate.\nAchieve higher rate, quality and lower cost of prototyping, experimentation, and concept pilots by leveraging Design Thinking, Agile methodologies, best practices and reuse.\nCreate Intellectual Property (IP) in the form of patents, publication of papers in the relevant areas that is tightly aligned to the strategic direction of the GSD.\nThought leadership in the application of the latest technology to address challenges in Public Safety and to pioneer innovations that promotes the eminence of the GSD.\n\nRequirements\n\nBachelor Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related technical field. Master’s degree is a plus.\n5 – 10 years development and delivery experience in back-end technologies and in one or more programming languages like Java, C/C++, C#.\n1 – 2 years demonstrable experience in large scale system design and building scalable, high performing and robust applications.\nGood knowledge in design patterns, data structures, multi-threading and high volume server side development.\nExperience with building RESTful services and micro-services.\nExperience with Docker, Kubernetes, or other container tools.\nExperience in CI/CD tools (Jerkins, GitLab CI), database technology (MySQL, PostgreSQL), cloud deployment technologies (Ansible, Puppet, Chef).\nExperience with developing applications on cloud architectures (AWS, Azure). Hands-on development in a serverless architecture (AWS Lamda) is a plus.\nExperience of working in agile, scrum and DevOps teams.\nProficient with code versioning tools like Git.\nStrong analytical skills and well-versed in problem solving skills.\nExperience in front end technologies like Angular, ReactJS, is a plus.\nKnowledge of iOS and Android development is a plus.\nGood communication skills.\nPossess can-do attitude, creativity and initiative", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<p><strong>Advisory/Software Engineer (Fresh Graduates are welcome to apply)</strong></p>\n\n<p>The Open Innovation Center (OIC) of Global Safety Division (GSD) leads disruptive idea generation, research, testing and prototyping with the goal of launching breakthrough products and services inspired by global trends and emerging technologies, contributing to a Safer City.</p>\n\n<p>Work location is at 21 Biopolis Road #05-01/02 Nucleos (nearest MRT station: One North or Buona Vista).</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nResponsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>\nActively engage in the creation of new disruptive and transformational products and services.</li><li>\nSenior members will lead squads (scrum teams) dedicated in the implementation of Proof-of-Concepts (POCs), Prototypes and Pilots with strategic customers.</li><li>\nPromote customer advocacy by engaging with strategic customers, country affiliates and business partners on the formulation of POCs, Prototypes and Pilots in associated documentation.</li><li>\nSupport the Technology Development Managers / Directors to prioritize concept requests at each stage of the OIC process (e.g. ideation, concept validation, agile prototyping).</li><li>\nHands-on Involvement in the roadmap planning, design, architecting and coding of the POCs, Prototypes and Pilots.</li><li>\nEngage in the whole DevOps lifecycle from the development, testing, deployment, maintenance and operations of products and services.</li><li>\nParticipate in the building and enhancement of a robust pipeline to support the automation of various development associated tasks to achieve continuous integration and delivery.</li><li>\nProactively devise innovative solutions by constantly broadening and deepening the skillsets, and attaining awareness of trends and development in the technical domain to address latent challenges faced by various industries.</li><li>\nIdentify best practices from industry and implement new and evolve methodology as appropriate.</li><li>\nAchieve higher rate, quality and lower cost of prototyping, experimentation, and concept pilots by leveraging Design Thinking, Agile methodologies, best practices and reuse.</li><li>\nCreate Intellectual Property (IP) in the form of patents, publication of papers in the relevant areas that is tightly aligned to the strategic direction of the GSD.</li><li>\nThought leadership in the application of the latest technology to address challenges in Public Safety and to pioneer innovations that promotes the eminence of the GSD.</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>\nRequirements</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>\nBachelor Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related technical field. Master’s degree is a plus.</li><li>\n5 – 10 years development and delivery experience in back-end technologies and in one or more programming languages like Java, C/C++, C#.</li><li>\n1 – 2 years demonstrable experience in large scale system design and building scalable, high performing and robust applications.</li><li>\nGood knowledge in design patterns, data structures, multi-threading and high volume server side development.</li><li>\nExperience with building RESTful services and micro-services.</li><li>\nExperience with Docker, Kubernetes, or other container tools.</li><li>\nExperience in CI/CD tools (Jerkins, GitLab CI), database technology (MySQL, PostgreSQL), cloud deployment technologies (Ansible, Puppet, Chef).</li><li>\nExperience with developing applications on cloud architectures (AWS, Azure). Hands-on development in a serverless architecture (AWS Lamda) is a plus.</li><li>\nExperience of working in agile, scrum and DevOps teams.</li><li>\nProficient with code versioning tools like Git.</li><li>\nStrong analytical skills and well-versed in problem solving skills.\n</li><li>Experience in front end technologies like Angular, ReactJS, is a plus.</li><li>\nKnowledge of iOS and Android development is a plus.</li><li>\nGood communication skills.</li><li>\nPossess can-do attitude, creativity and initiative</li></ul>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9747389, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b49e0aac8f882d5c&from=serp&vjs=3", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "TechSkills Accelerator"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951231-97cc1a52ae912725", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=127d65b0a13e9501&fccid=e140ab80cac32f76&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Dev Manager", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Gold Coast QLD"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-30T00:00:00", "description": "DESCRIPTION\n\nEverything we do is recorded, collected, mined, profiled, stored, targeted and sold. The balance of power has shifted to the cabal of tech giants and data miners who overtly or covertly control what you see, whom you connect with, what you read, click, and care about. Something has to be done! At Anonyome Labs, we are building the tools that shift control of your personal and private information from the big data miners back to you, the user. If you want to be a part of something innovative, challenging, meaningful and, most of all, something that matters…then it’s time to talk.\n\nJob Description\n\nAnonyome is looking for a development manager who will work with architects, team leads, and product managers to help guide the scrum teams towards continual improvement and craftsmanship. You will develop a deep understanding of the people you lead and the practices and technologies we leverage. You will apply your expertise in planning, prioritising and executing the company's strategic objectives. You will support the career growth and self-development of your direct reports, as well as foster an inclusive and collaborative environment where your team will perform their most impactful work.\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nOwn the growth, quality and output of the Platform engineering teams in our GC office.\nPlay a key role in recruiting and hiring the best engineering talent to support our continued growth in the market.\nManage the goals and career paths of your people, conducting regular 1-on-1s and giving feedback and guidance.\nOwn and continuously refine the processes and communication strategies your team uses to build and support products.\nWork with a product manager, architects and other development managers to ensure that the roadmap is realistic and understood\nWork with your manager to turn the roadmap into staffing needs and a recruiting/hiring funnel.\nBe an ongoing contributor to our software platforms (e.g. Javascript, Typescript, Java, iOS, Android), though it is not expected that you will be coding full-time.\nCollaborate with the engineering managers in our other labs to ensure consistency and constant improvement across the organisation.\n\nMust-haves:\n\nB.S. in Computer Science or a related technical field\n5+ years experience building modern software platforms in a growth-stage start up, consumer product company or enterprise engineering environment.\n3+ years experience managing and growing software engineering teams as a people manager - experience as a hiring manager a big plus.\nExperience with Amazon Web Services (EC2, CloudFront, CloudWatch, VPC, CloudFormation, etc.)\nExcellence in communicating complex concepts (written and oral)\n\nBonus points:\n\nExperience scaling highly available software platforms\nExperience in privacy, security, messaging, telephony, etc.\nWorking knowledge of API design and distributed back-end systems.\n\nFinally, we expect you to score well on our \"Stuff That Matters\":\n\nBELIEVE: In the company’s mission, in the team, and in your equity\n\nONE TEAM, ONE DREAM: We win together and lose individually\n\nOK WITH AMBIGUITY: Comfortable making decisions with very little information\n\nCURIOSITY: Seek out answers inside and outside the building\n\nHUMILITY: Assume you don’t have all the answers and seek to understand\n\nBIAS TO ACTION: When in doubt, DO SOMETHING NOW\n\nOWNERSHIP: When in doubt, TAKE IT ON.\n\nWe offer company stock options, private health plans, cool office space, catered lunches, fun exciting work environment overlooking the beach of the Gold Coast, and the opportunity to learn from leading privacy and security experts with a combined patent filing count of 60+ in the privacy/security area. If you’re interested in changing the world, we’d love to talk to you.", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<h2><strong>DESCRIPTION</strong></h2>\n\n<p>Everything we do is recorded, collected, mined, profiled, stored, targeted and sold. The balance of power has shifted to the cabal of tech giants and data miners who overtly or covertly control what you see, whom you connect with, what you read, click, and care about. Something has to be done! At Anonyome Labs, we are building the tools that shift control of your personal and private information from the big data miners back to you, the user. If you want to be a part of something innovative, challenging, meaningful and, most of all, something that matters…then it’s time to talk.</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nJob Description</strong></p>\n\n<p>Anonyome is looking for a development manager who will work with architects, team leads, and product managers to help guide the scrum teams towards continual improvement and craftsmanship. You will develop a deep understanding of the people you lead and the practices and technologies we leverage. You will apply your expertise in planning, prioritising and executing the company's strategic objectives. You will support the career growth and self-development of your direct reports, as well as foster an inclusive and collaborative environment where your team will perform their most impactful work.</p>\n\n<h2><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></h2>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>\nOwn the growth, quality and output of the Platform engineering teams in our GC office.</li><li>\nPlay a key role in recruiting and hiring the best engineering talent to support our continued growth in the market.</li><li>\nManage the goals and career paths of your people, conducting regular 1-on-1s and giving feedback and guidance.</li><li>\nOwn and continuously refine the processes and communication strategies your team uses to build and support products.</li><li>\nWork with a product manager, architects and other development managers to ensure that the roadmap is realistic and understood</li><li>\nWork with your manager to turn the roadmap into staffing needs and a recruiting/hiring funnel.</li><li>\nBe an ongoing contributor to our software platforms (e.g. Javascript, Typescript, Java, iOS, Android), though it is not expected that you will be coding full-time.</li><li>\nCollaborate with the engineering managers in our other labs to ensure consistency and constant improvement across the organisation.</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>\nMust-haves:</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>\nB.S. in Computer Science or a related technical field</li><li>\n5+ years experience building modern software platforms in a growth-stage start up, consumer product company or enterprise engineering environment.</li><li>\n3+ years experience managing and growing software engineering teams as a people manager - experience as a hiring manager a big plus.</li><li>\nExperience with Amazon Web Services (EC2, CloudFront, CloudWatch, VPC, CloudFormation, etc.)</li><li>\nExcellence in communicating complex concepts (written and oral)</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>\nBonus points:</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>\nExperience scaling highly available software platforms</li><li>\nExperience in privacy, security, messaging, telephony, etc.</li><li>\nWorking knowledge of API design and distributed back-end systems.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Finally, we expect you to score well on our \"Stuff That Matters\":</p>\n\n<p>BELIEVE: In the company’s mission, in the team, and in your equity</p>\n\n<p>ONE TEAM, ONE DREAM: We win together and lose individually</p>\n\n<p>OK WITH AMBIGUITY: Comfortable making decisions with very little information</p>\n\n<p>CURIOSITY: Seek out answers inside and outside the building</p>\n\n<p>HUMILITY: Assume you don’t have all the answers and seek to understand</p>\n\n<p>BIAS TO ACTION: When in doubt, DO SOMETHING NOW</p>\n\n<p>OWNERSHIP: When in doubt, TAKE IT ON.</p>\n\n<p>We offer company stock options, private health plans, cool office space, catered lunches, fun exciting work environment overlooking the beach of the Gold Coast, and the opportunity to learn from leading privacy and security experts with a combined patent filing count of 60+ in the privacy/security area. If you’re interested in changing the world, we’d love to talk to you.</p>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9831367, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=127d65b0a13e9501&from=serp&vjs=3", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "Gold Coast QLD"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951231-5275aadd4abf8637", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=bc0b83bca4a63fdc&fccid=772a1485bbbe4156&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Project Specialist , Adelaide", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Adelaide Region SA"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-30T00:00:00", "description": "Project Specialist , Adelaide - (20009046)\n\nDescription JOB SUMMARY\n\nThe Project Specialist performs administrative and supportive activities assigned by the Project Lead to ensure the contracted services and expectations are carried out by the project team in accordance with executed contracts and the customers’ expectations.\n\nJOB RESPONSIBILITIES\n\nSet-up, maintain and/or close out project files and study information ((e.g., regulatory documents, Trial Master File (TMF), enrollment, Adverse Events (AEs)/Serious Adverse Events (SAEs), site supplies, Institutional Review Board re-approvals, data queries) on a variety of databases and systems.\n\nAttends, participates, prepares and distributes meeting minutes and action items for both internal and external meetings (sponsor, trusted process, functional, investigator meetings). Follows up with team members on action items to closure.\n\nMaintains timely and effective communication among team members and site staff. Keeps Project Leadership and Clinical Research Associates (CRAs) fully appraised of sites and study status. May contact site staff as needed for critical information.\n\nProvide administrative support to Project Leads and functional leads.\n\nEnsure all study documents are archived based on the appropriate guidelines and policy.\n\nProvide support for quality assurance activities, including preparation for audits and internal review, prepare documentation and follow through to resolution on actionable issues.\n\nQualifications\n\nQUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS\n\nAssociates Degree (or equivalent) level of qualification in life sciences, Medicine, Pharmacy, Nursing or related field or equivalent combination of education and experience\n\nKnowledge of Good Clinical Practice/ICH guidelines and other applicable regulatory requirements.\n\nStrong organizational skills.\n\nAbility to manage time and work independently.\n\nHigh proficiency with full MS Office Applications.\n\nStrong communication, presentation, interpersonal skills, both written and spoken, with an ability to inform, influence, convince, and persuade\n\nAbility to travel if necessary preferred (approximately 5%)\nHigh level of competence in English language\n\nDisclaimer:\n\nTasks, duties, and responsibilities as listed in this job description are not exhaustive. The Company, at its sole discretion and with no prior notice, may assign other tasks, duties, and job responsibilities. Equivalent experience, skills, and/or education will also be considered so qualifications of incumbents may differ from those listed in the Job Description. The Company, at its sole discretion, will determine what constitutes as equivalent to the qualifications described above. Further, nothing contained herein should be construed to create an employment contract. Occasionally, required skills/experiences for jobs are expressed in brief terms. Any language contained herein is intended to fully comply with all obligations imposed by the legislation of each country in which it operates, including the implementation of the EU Equality Directive, in relation to the recruitment and employment of its employees.\n\nPrimary Location: Asia Pacific - AUS-Adelaide-159-Port-Road\n\nJob: Clinical Project Management\n\nSchedule: Full-time\n\nTravel: No\n\nEmployee Status: Regular", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<p><strong>Project Specialist , Adelaide</strong> <strong>-</strong> <strong>(</strong><strong>20009046</strong><strong>)</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>\nDescription</strong>\n<strong>\nJOB SUMMARY</strong></p>\n\n<p>The Project Specialist performs administrative and supportive activities assigned by the Project Lead to ensure the contracted services and expectations are carried out by the project team in accordance with executed contracts and the customers’ expectations.</p>\n\n<p><strong>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES</strong><br></p>\n\n<ul><li> Set-up, maintain and/or close out project files and study information ((e.g., regulatory documents, Trial Master File (TMF), enrollment, Adverse Events (AEs)/Serious Adverse Events (SAEs), site supplies, Institutional Review Board re-approvals, data queries) on a variety of databases and systems.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Attends, participates, prepares and distributes meeting minutes and action items for both internal and external meetings (sponsor, trusted process, functional, investigator meetings). Follows up with team members on action items to closure.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Maintains timely and effective communication among team members and site staff. Keeps Project Leadership and Clinical Research Associates (CRAs) fully appraised of sites and study status. May contact site staff as needed for critical information.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Provide administrative support to Project Leads and functional leads.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Ensure all study documents are archived based on the appropriate guidelines and policy.\n</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Provide support for quality assurance activities, including preparation for audits and internal review, prepare documentation and follow through to resolution on actionable issues.<br>\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong><br></p>\n\n<p><strong>\n QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li> Associates Degree (or equivalent) level of qualification in life sciences, Medicine, Pharmacy, Nursing or related field or equivalent combination of education and experience</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Knowledge of Good Clinical Practice/ICH guidelines and other applicable regulatory requirements.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Strong organizational skills.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Ability to manage time and work independently.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> High proficiency with full MS Office Applications.</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Strong communication, presentation, interpersonal skills, both written and spoken, with an ability to inform, influence, convince, and persuade</li></ul>\n\n<ul><li> Ability to travel if necessary preferred (approximately 5%)</li><li> High level of competence in English language</li></ul>\n\n<p>Disclaimer:</p>\n\n<p>Tasks, duties, and responsibilities as listed in this job description are not exhaustive. The Company, at its sole discretion and with no prior notice, may assign other tasks, duties, and job responsibilities. Equivalent experience, skills, and/or education will also be considered so qualifications of incumbents may differ from those listed in the Job Description. The Company, at its sole discretion, will determine what constitutes as equivalent to the qualifications described above. Further, nothing contained herein should be construed to create an employment contract. Occasionally, required skills/experiences for jobs are expressed in brief terms. Any language contained herein is intended to fully comply with all obligations imposed by the legislation of each country in which it operates, including the implementation of the EU Equality Directive, in relation to the recruitment and employment of its employees.</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nPrimary Location</strong><strong>:</strong> Asia Pacific - AUS-Adelaide-159-Port-Road</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nJob</strong><strong>:</strong> Clinical Project Management</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nSchedule</strong><strong>:</strong> Full-time</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nTravel</strong><strong>:</strong> No</p>\n\n<p><strong>\nEmployee Status</strong><strong>:</strong> Regular</p>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.98150235, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bc0b83bca4a63fdc&fr