chniques\n</li><li>Ensures requirements meet market and/or business needs\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Manage:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Prepares requirements documentation\n</li><li>Presents requirements in an understandable format\n</li><li>Obtains needed approvals\n</li><li>Traces requirements\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Requirements Planning:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Plans business analysis approach based on project complexity, risks, assumptions, dependencies.\n</li><li>Defines the plan to deliver requirements, including elicitation, analysis and management\n</li><li>Builds and manages relationships with stakeholders based on an understanding of their influence and needs.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Strategy and Product Planning:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Provides input in feature/function to the Product Manager in developing the product roadmap\n</li><li>Provides input to Product Marketing Manager on case studies and customer reference implementations\n</li><li>Continuously develops domain knowledge, depth and breadth, in the payments industry, ACI products, customer base and applied technology.\n</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned.\n</li><li>Understand and adhere to all corporate policies to include but not limited to the ACI Code of Business Conduct and Ethics.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Knowledge, Skills and Experience required for the job:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or Business Administration or equivalent experience.\n</li><li>2 years in an industry related role such as technical support, product management or product development with exposure to marketing, or comparable work experience.\n</li><li>Knowledge and experience in most aspects of business analysis.\n</li><li>Some knowledge of the payments industry, customer base and applied technology.\n</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.\n</li><li>Excellent skills in negotiating and collaborating to give guidance to the development organization.\n</li><li>Creation of quality, easy to understand papers and presentations.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Preferred Knowledge, Skills and Experience needed for the job:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Aware of technology used by ACI solutions.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p><strong>Work Environment:\n</strong></p>\n\n<ul><li>Travel required</li></ul>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9858444, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=037d31d148419ba4&from=serp&vjs=3", "employmentType": "Part-time", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "ACI Worldwide"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}
{"query": {"id": "1611376951233-8e226dba68957e6a", "domain": "indeed.com", "userAgent": "scrapinghub-autoextract/0.6.0 aiohttp/3.7.3", "userQuery": {"url": "https://au.indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=17753882fb253009&fccid=d12adad945f8d28d&vjs=3", "pageType": "jobPosting", "articleBodyRaw": false}}, "webPage": {"inLanguages": [{"code": "en"}]}, "jobPosting": {"title": "Superintendent Geology Oak Dam", "jobLocation": {"raw": "Roxby Downs SA"}, "datePosted": "2021-01-14T04:42:45.217316", "description": "About BHP\n\nAt BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential. With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success. Come and be a part of this success.\n\nOlympic Dam\n\nAs one of Australia’s largest underground mines and most complex minerals processing operations, Olympic Dam is globally unique in that we produce Copper, Uranium, Gold and Silver. Oak Dam is an exciting exploration discovery located 65km south east of Olympic Dam with the potential to significantly contribute to the long-term growth strategy for the Asset. The local township of Roxby Downs is an active and progressive community offering a variety of modern, well-equipped housing, educational, heal, sporting, leisure, shopping and cultural facilities.\n\nAbout the role\n\nWith the continued success of our Oak Dam exploration discovery through 2020, the project has transferred to the Minerals Australia Planning & Technical team as an advanced exploration project to undertake the next phase directional drilling program, technically evaluate resource characteristics and assess development pathways. Accordingly we are seeking a highly motivated Superintendent Geology to join our team reporting to the Manager Oak Dam, Olympic Dam. This is an outstanding oppurtunity to lead the exploration strategy and execution for the next phase advanced exploration and resource definition program for an exciting South Australian mining prospect. Based in our award winning Adelaide office, the position offers flexible conditions and a balance of time on the Oak Dam Explration Licence and Olympic Dam site providing supervision and field leadership. This diverse range of work will see you positiively influence business portfolio decisions.\n\nTo excel in this role you will require:\n\nDemonstrated knowledge of Iron-Oxide-Copper-Gold mineral systems\nA track record of leading advanced greenfield exploration programs with deep directional core drilling experience\nJORC documentation and reporting experience covering Exploration Results, and geological inputs to Mineral Resources through to Ore Reserves\nExperience with geological modelling software (ie Leapfrog)\nProficient stakeholder management and project management capabilities.\n\nCore responsibilities of the role include (but are not limited to):\n\nHealth, Safety and Environment leadership\nLeading the Phase 4 advanced exploration strategy and diamond drilling program\nDrilling Services contractor technical supervision and collaboration to ensure the objectives of the drilling program are achieved\nDefinition, coordination and delivery of technical data capture to support resource engineering evaluations including geotechnical, geo metallurgical and hydrogeological\nGeological model development, resource range analysis and review with internal and external reviewers.\n\nAbout you\n\nYou will have tertiary qualifications in Geology, Earth Sciences or a related science field ideally with 10+ years’ experience in minerals exploration and resource development projects. A focus on value based decision making, project management skills, strong leadership capability and exposure to approvals processes are also desirable.\n\nYour superior stakeholder engagement will foster collaborative working relationships across our Geoscience & Resource Engineering, Studies & Access, HSE and operational teams. You will have knowledge to apply critical thinking to the development and the ability to communicate effectively across disciplines and organisational levels to create buy-in and influence outcomes. You will have demonstrated leadership capability, and the strong interpersonal skills to engage and listen to the diverse range of employees and stakeholders within our business.\n\nYou will be a performance and achievement orientated professional, who is motivated by exceeding expectations through delivering excellent results.\n\nSupporting a Diverse Workforce\n\nAt BHP, we recognise that we are strengthened by diversity. We care committed to providing a work environment in which everyone is included, treated fairly and with respect. We are an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from women and Indigenous people.\n\nWe know there are many aspects of our employees’ lives that are important, and work is only one of these, so we offer benefits to enable your work to fit with your life. These benefits include flexible working options, a generous paid parental leave policy and other extended leave entitlements.\n\nImportant\n\nThe safety of BHP’s people and our candidates is our number one priority. To protect the health and safety of vulnerable persons in line with current Government advice, you may be asked to undergo a COVID-19 related health assessment.\n\nDue to the unfolding circumstances of COVID-19 and the Government regulations in place to deal with the pandemic, your working location and/or roster as advertised in the advert may be temporarily subject to change whilst the government regulations are in place. This is to ensure the health and safety of our workforce, and to implement effective social distancing measures. These changes if applicable will be discussed at screening and interview stage.", "descriptionHtml": "<article>\n\n<h2><strong>About BHP</strong></h2>\n\n<p>At BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential. With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success. Come and be a part of this success.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Olympic Dam</p>\n\n<p>As one of Australia’s largest underground mines and most complex minerals processing operations, Olympic Dam is globally unique in that we produce Copper, Uranium, Gold and Silver. Oak Dam is an exciting exploration discovery located 65km south east of Olympic Dam with the potential to significantly contribute to the long-term growth strategy for the Asset. The local township of Roxby Downs is an active and progressive community offering a variety of modern, well-equipped housing, educational, heal, sporting, leisure, shopping and cultural facilities.</p>\n\n<h2><strong>\nAbout the role</strong></h2>\n\n<p>With the continued success of our Oak Dam exploration discovery through 2020, the project has transferred to the Minerals Australia Planning &amp; Technical team as an advanced exploration project to undertake the next phase directional drilling program, technically evaluate resource characteristics and assess development pathways. Accordingly we are seeking a highly motivated Superintendent Geology to join our team reporting to the Manager Oak Dam, Olympic Dam. This is an outstanding oppurtunity to lead the exploration strategy and execution for the next phase advanced exploration and resource definition program for an exciting South Australian mining prospect. Based in our award winning Adelaide office, the position offers flexible conditions and a balance of time on the Oak Dam Explration Licence and Olympic Dam site providing supervision and field leadership. This diverse range of work will see you positiively influence business portfolio decisions.<br></p>\n\n<p>To excel in this role you will require:</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<ul><li>Demonstrated knowledge of Iron-Oxide-Copper-Gold mineral systems</li>\n<li>A track record of leading advanced greenfield exploration programs with deep directional core drilling experience</li>\n<li>JORC documentation and reporting experience covering Exploration Results, and geological inputs to Mineral Resources through to Ore Reserves</li>\n<li>Experience with geological modelling software (ie Leapfrog)</li>\n<li>Proficient stakeholder management and project management capabilities.</li></ul>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Core responsibilities of the role include (but are not limited to):</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<ul><li>Health, Safety and Environment leadership</li>\n<li>Leading the Phase 4 advanced exploration strategy and diamond drilling program</li>\n<li>Drilling Services contractor technical supervision and collaboration to ensure the objectives of the drilling program are achieved</li>\n<li>Definition, coordination and delivery of technical data capture to support resource engineering evaluations including geotechnical, geo metallurgical and hydrogeological</li>\n<li>Geological model development, resource range analysis and review with internal and external reviewers.</li></ul>\n\n<h2><strong>About you</strong></h2>\n\n<p>You will have tertiary qualifications in Geology, Earth Sciences or a related science field ideally with 10+ years’ experience in minerals exploration and resource development projects. A focus on value based decision making, project management skills, strong leadership capability and exposure to approvals processes are also desirable.<br></p>\n\n<p>Your superior stakeholder engagement will foster collaborative working relationships across our Geoscience &amp; Resource Engineering, Studies &amp; Access, HSE and operational teams. You will have knowledge to apply critical thinking to the development and the ability to communicate effectively across disciplines and organisational levels to create buy-in and influence outcomes. You will have demonstrated leadership capability, and the strong interpersonal skills to engage and listen to the diverse range of employees and stakeholders within our business.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>You will be a performance and achievement orientated professional, who is motivated by exceeding expectations through delivering excellent results.</p>\n\n<h2><strong>\nSupporting a Diverse Workforce</strong></h2>\n\n<p>At BHP, we recognise that we are strengthened by diversity. We care committed to providing a work environment in which everyone is included, treated fairly and with respect. We are an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from women and Indigenous people.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>We know there are many aspects of our employees’ lives that are important, and work is only one of these, so we offer benefits to enable your work to fit with your life. These benefits include flexible working options, a generous paid parental leave policy and other extended leave entitlements.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Important</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>The safety of BHP’s people and our candidates is our number one priority. To protect the health and safety of vulnerable persons in line with current Government advice, you may be asked to undergo a COVID-19 related health assessment.</p>\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p>Due to the unfolding circumstances of COVID-19 and the Government regulations in place to deal with the pandemic, your working location and/or roster as advertised in the advert may be temporarily subject to change whilst the government regulations are in place. This is to ensure the health and safety of our workforce, and to implement effective social distancing measures. These changes if applicable will be discussed at screening and interview stage.</p>\n\n</article>", "probability": 0.9763765, "url": "https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=17753882fb253009&from=serp&vjs=3", "hiringOrganization": {"raw": "Roxby Downs SA"}}, "algorithmVersion": "21.1.0"}